children.text: The sewer overflow relief gully (ORG) has been installed too high, with less than 150mm separation to the lowest fixture in the building.
The Victorian Building Authority’s Technical Solution Sheet 3.05 warns that failure to protect against sewage discharge is a major fault item, and states that

‘A minimum vertical separation of 150mm must be provided between the lowest fixture (usually the shower grate or floor waste) and the spill level of an overflow relief gully riser to ensure that the dwelling is protected from sewer surcharge (see Figure 1)’ ;

The ORG will need to be moved to provide a minimum 150mm separation to the lowest fixture, whilst remaining a minimum of 75mm above any paving to prevent ingress of surface water into the sewer system, in accordance with Australian Standard AS 3500.2 – Plumbing and Drainage.
